`@JsonIgnore` is used to ignore the logical property used in serialization and deserialization. `@JsonIgnore` can be used at **setter**, **getter** or **field**.  

If you add `@JsonIgnore` to a field or its getter method, the field is not going to be serialized.

Sample POJO:

    class User {
        @JsonIgnore
        private int id;
        private String name;
        public int getId() {
            return id;
        }
        @JsonIgnore
        public void setId(int id) {
            this.id = id;
        }
        public String getName() {
            return name;
        }
        public void setName(String name) {
            this.name = name;
        }  
    }

Sample code for serialization:

    ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
    User user = new User();
    user.setId(2);
    user.setName(&quot;Bob&quot;);
